Text: Beta races toward the top of the tower.

As soon as Beta is in range, she aims a blow at
Elisabeth's neck.

Elisabeth's head is severed from her body, and she
staggers, losing her balance.
Beta shouts, and No. 664 appears to protect Claire.

Beta waits until No. 644 is out of range before
launching a dagger at Elisabeth.
The dagger lands between Elisabeth's eyes...
Still breathing. But first aid may not be enough!

I see. Unfortunately...I doubt we'll be able to
simply walk away...

Our master hasn't shown up yet. There must be an
important reason why he had to prioritize some other
matter...

Which means he implicitly left the situation here for
me to handle.

Beta hadn't realized it until it was too late.
Because of this, the worst-case scenario is
unfolding before her eyes.
(If Master Shadow's sister were to die...)

Time to see what I can do against the legendary Blood
Queen...

No. 664, keep treating her. No. 665, No. 666, back me
up!
No. 665 and No. 666 make their way towards Elisabeth.
They swing their swords down on her.

But Elisabeth catches the blades with her hands,
stopping their trajectory.

No. 665 and No. 666 try to force their blades out,
but Elisabeth's muscle sinews holds them firmly.
She throws another dagger at Elisabeth.
(We might just be able to win this...)

Beta's initial impression was that fighting the
Blood Queen one-on-one would be impossible.
Even with three of her subordinates, she'd been
expecting a rough fight.

In reality, she is a fearsome opponent. However,
she is easier to fight than Beta had anticipated.

The rookies were exceeding her expectations as well.
It's just as Lambda had told her—between No. 664's
leadership, No. 665's wisdom and intellect, and
No. 666's battle prowess, they made for a solid team.
You people are strong, I'll give you that...
But she... She has always been...
At that moment, Elisabeth's eyes open slightly.

The Blood Queen's magic rises explosively, causing
the very air to tremble. Beta grimaces, feeling the
power radiating from the vampire.
So this is the Blood Queen.

Something cold runs up Beta's spine. She can feel in
her skin just how fundamentally outmatched they
are. The Blood Queen is truly a monster.

The only person who could possibly stand up to such a
creature is her master.
Well, well. Despite her cute looks,
we have quite the monster here.
Guess I should stick around for this...
Don't go gettin' this party started...

Feelers wrap around Juggernaut, lifting him into the
air.
Juggernaut's massive body flies through the air.
What on earth are you doing?
Large amounts of magic gather around Elisabeth.

Suddenly, the blood surrounding Elisabeth rains down,
assaulting everyone present.
Beta transforms slime into a protective shield.

The shield unceremoniously breaks, and the blood
comes raining down.

Elisabeth's attack ceases, and a red mist envelops
their surroundings.
Why did you take all the damage? Are you an idiot?
I'm guessing you can't use that thing anymore.
Beta has sustained injuries on her arms and thighs.
And so is the Blood Queen.

(Even after expending so much magic, she shows no
signs of fatigue...)
(Could it be that by taking our blood,)

(Given the situation, no matter how we fight, even if
we all work together, we can't possibly win.)
Don't you have something you need to accomplish?
Right now, you need to value your life.

There's no need to win. After all, they have Master
Shadow. All Beta has to do is buy time until he shows
up.

No matter what happens, no matter whom he has to
face, her master is her absolute.

She squares off against the Blood Queen and gathers
as much magic in her dagger as she can.
Her power suddenly starts running wild.

She tries dropping her output to regain control, but
her rampaging magic refuses to be quelled.
A familiar, unpleasant pain runs across her body.
Her skin starts turning black around her wounds.

Now that she knows the cause, Beta immediately
changes how she's trying to suppress her magic.
She's largely successful in getting it to settle down,
but she's still having a hard time controlling it.
Is she manipulating the blood of the possessed...

How dare she defile Master Shadow's acts of kindness
in such a way!
